    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Vibration Damper, Oil Pump, and
        Cooling System - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
            <title>Front Cover</title>
            <figure id="f3000625" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover crankcase dowels</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install front cover crankcase dowels.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Dowels may become lodged in front cover. Remove dowels and install in crankcase. If dowels are
                        bent, replace with new ones.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3000626" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Locations for Liquid Gasket (RTV) application</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, install and torque gasket and cover within five minutes of applying
                        Liquid Gasket (RTV).
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_257.xml" xrefid="t390001003">Liquid Gasket (RTV)</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t390001003"/>
                    to joining surfaces of crankcase and lower crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new front cover gasket on the crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000628" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover and gasket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align front cover with crankcase dowels.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000629" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Front cover module retaining bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 35 (17)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install seventeen M8 x 35 bolts and finger tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten seventeen M8 x 35 bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_256.xml" xrefid="e30006b">special torque
                        <xref refid="e30006b"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3000630" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06041.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Heater feed tube O-ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate a new heater feed tube O-ring with the recommended coolant.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not lubricate heater feed tube O-ring with engine oil. Oil
                        produces swelling of O-ring, resulting in leakage.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f3000631" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj06/J06042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Heater feed tube assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Nut, M10</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M6 x 14</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install heater feed tube into front cover while aligning bracket slot with stud at
                    lifting eye. Install bolt (M6 x 14) into front cover and tighten to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="te265appb02">standard torque
                        <xref refid="te265appb02"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    . Tighten nut to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_256.xml" xrefid="e30006b">special torque
                        <xref refid="e30006b"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
